	abstract = {This paper investigates the problem of cooperative moving-target enclosing control for multi-agent systems with nonholonomic constraint, where multiple agents enclose a moving target with an unknown time-varying velocity and maintain even spacing on the desired orbit. A novel cooperative circular formation control protocol is designed for each agent using local relative information and its neighbor information only without communication between the target and agent. Time-varying constraints on the formation tracking errors are considered due to limited sensor detection range and collision avoidance. Consequently, universal barrier Lyapunov functions are introduced to the controller synthesis such that formation tracking errors converge into a small neighborhood of zero. Finally, 3D simulations based on Gazebo simulator are conducted to demonstrate the effectiveness of the proposed control protocol.},
